The latter situation of data and sample transfer is what happens most commonly, though providing access and benefit does not necessarily take place. Although data is targeted to be open access, data and sample flow is almost always unidirectional, from LMICs to HICs ( 
 Serwadda 
  et al., 2018
 ). Deepening concerns about exploitation, fairness and access to benefits from data have ultimately led to severe impediments to critically important data sharing between countries ( 
 Caulfield 
  et al., 2014
 ; 
 Sedyaningsih 
  et al., 2008
 ). The concerns regarding governance of international data sharing revolve around several different aspects of this fear of exploitation.
